# Physics-Informed RIR Generation Framework  Architecture

## Entry points

- **Single entry point:** RIR_Project.ipynb  thin orchestration layer that imports the underlying 
ir_project Python package. The package lives under src/rir_project and can be edited directly in Colab or locally; the notebook begins with !pip install -q -e . to install it in editable mode. This retains the convenience of a notebook while keeping the core code modular and reviewable. A pyproject.toml/setup.py is included to support pip install for Colab.

## High-level structure

The notebook implements a **Physics-Informed RIR Generation Framework**: room parameters  neural models + differentiable FDN  Room Impulse Responses. Code is organized into **six sequential phases**:

| Phase | Name                          | Main components |
|-------|-------------------------------|-----------------|
| 1     | Data pipeline                 | Helpers (_parse_json_field, compute_edc, compute_multiband_edc, compute_room_modes, downsample_edc_tensor), RIRMegaDataset, CachedRIRDataset, 
ir_collate_fn, get_dataloader |
| 2     | LSTM EDC predictor            | MultibandEDCPredictor (LSTM + BatchNorm1d, outputs multiband EDC) |
| 3     | Physics-informed loss         | EDCReconstructionLoss, continuity_residual, momentum_residual, PhysicsInformedRIRLoss |
| 4     | Differentiable FDN            | _hadamard_matrix, DifferentiableFDN (fractional delays, **log-constrained delay lengths** to maintain differentiability). Early/late bifurcation via EarlyReflectionNet optionally splits the first 50250ms processing from the recursive late-reverb FDN. |
| 5     | Training loop                 | TrainingConfig (dataclass), RIRTrainer (dataloaders, models, criterion, AMP, 	rain_one_epoch, alidate, it) |
| 6     | LSTMFDN bridge & synthesis   | EDCToFDNMapper, ConditionedFDN, SignStickyPhaseReconstructor, RIRSynthesiser, plus refinement/inference helpers |

## Data flow pipeline

`mermaid
flowchart LR
  subgraph ingest [Ingest]
    HF[HF mandipgoswami/rirmega]
    CSV[metadata CSV]
  end
  subgraph phase1 [Phase 1]
    RIRMega[RIRMegaDataset]
    Cache[CachedRIRDataset]
    DL[DataLoader + rir_collate_fn]
  end
  subgraph phase2_4 [Phases 2-4]
    LSTM[MultibandEDCPredictor]
    Loss[PhysicsInformedRIRLoss]
    FDN[DifferentiableFDN optional]
  end
  subgraph phase5 [Phase 5]
    Trainer[RIRTrainer]
  end
  subgraph phase6 [Phase 6]
    Bridge[EDCToFDNMapper]
    CondFDN[ConditionedFDN]
    PhaseRecon[SignStickyPhaseReconstructor]
    Synth[RIRSynthesiser]
  end
  HF --> RIRMega
  CSV --> RIRMega
  RIRMega --> Cache --> DL
  DL --> Trainer
  Trainer --> LSTM
  LSTM --> Loss
  FDN --> Loss
  LSTM --> Bridge --> CondFDN
  CondFDN --> PhaseRecon --> Synth
`

- **Training path:** HuggingFace AudioFolder+metadata CSV  decode/pad/truncate RIR  SchroederEDC (broadband+multiband)+room modes  RIRMegaDataset  optional CachedRIRDataset  DataLoader (
ir_collate_fn)  RIRTrainer batches (x_batch, y_batch)  LSTM predicts edc_pred  PhysicsInformedRIRLoss (EDC+continuity+momentum; optional FDNEDC loss).

- **Inference/synthesis path:** Room params X  MultibandEDCPredictor  edc_pred  EDCToFDNMapper  FDN params (log_kappa, alpha, beta)  ConditionedFDN (late reverb)+early reflections  SignStickyPhaseReconstructor  full RIR from RIRSynthesiser.

## Data contracts (tensor schema)

- **InputX:** [INPUT_DIM]=24: [L, W, H, src_xyz(3), mic_xyz(3), a_broad, a_125..a_4k(6), mode_count_300, f_schroeder, f_1st_axial, mean_ax_spacing, std_ax_spacing, modal_overlap, tang_ax_ratio, log_vol].
- **TargetsY:** dict with metrics [METRICS_DIM]=10, 
ir [max_len], edc [max_len], edc_mb [num_time_steps, num_bands], 
ir_length scalar. Batch: same keys, batch dim first (e.g. [B, 24], [B, METRICS_DIM], [B, max_len]).
- **Constants:** INPUT_DIM = 16 + MODAL_FEAT_DIM (24), MODAL_FEAT_DIM = 8, METRICS_DIM = 10, OCTAVE_BANDS (6 bands), DEFAULT_MAX_RIR_LEN = 32_000, DEVICE from 	orch.device("cuda" if ... else "cpu").

## Design patterns

- **Config object:** TrainingConfig dataclass holds all training/hyperparameters; passed into RIRTrainer.
- **Orchestrator/harness:** RIRTrainer builds dataloaders, models, criterion, optimiser, AMP; runs 	rain_one_epoch/alidate/it.
- **Factory:** get_dataloader(...) returns a configured DataLoader (optionally wrapping with CachedRIRDataset).
- **Pipeline (procedural):** Phases16 run in notebook order; later phases assume earlier cells have been run.
- **PyTorch conventions:** Dataset (__getitem__  single sample), custom collate_fn for batching, 
n.Module for all models, device via DEVICE and .to(device).
